defmodule Solution do
  @spec beautiful_indices(s :: String.t, a :: String.t, b :: String.t, k :: integer) :: [integer]
  def beautiful_indices(s, a, b, k) do
    {a_positions, b_positions} = Enum.reduce(0..(String.length(s) - 1), {[], []}, fn i, {acc_a, acc_b} ->
      acc_a = if String.slice(s, i, String.length(a)) == a, do: [i | acc_a], else: acc_a
      acc_b = if String.slice(s, i, String.length(b)) == b, do: [i | acc_b], else: acc_b
      {acc_a, acc_b}
    end)

    a_positions
    |> Enum.reverse()
    |> Enum.filter(fn i ->
      Enum.any?(b_positions, fn j -> abs(i - j) <= k end)
    end)
  end
end
